  "dataFlow": "1. INBOUND TRIGGERS: (a) Human submits repo_url+brief via Next.js dashboard → POST /api/build; (b) GitHub push/PR fires HMAC-verified webhook → POST /api/webhook; (c) Linear issue transitions to Todo → webhook or autonomy poller (5-min poll); (d) Phill sends Telegram message → inbox poller writes to .harness/telegram-inbox/ → watchdog drains on 30-min cycle; (e) Cron engine fires scheduled Pi-SEO scans/monitors/board meetings. 2. SESSION CREATION: create_session() validates repo_url, checks concurrent session cap (TAO_MAX_SESSIONS), instantiates BuildSession in _sessions dict, atomically writes session JSON to disk. 3. BUILD PIPELINE: run_build() executes 5 phases via Claude Agent SDK with bypassPermissions: (i) Clone repo via git into app/workspaces/; (ii) Plan phase: Opus model decomposes brief into TaskSpecs; (iii) Generate phase: Sonnet model executes tasks in workspace, commits changes; (iv) Evaluate phase: Sonnet model grades git diff on 4 dimensions, retries up to max_retries if below threshold; (v) Ship phase: gates on evaluator score, pushes to GitHub via PAT. 4. STREAMING: Each phase emits output_lines to BuildSession, streamed to browser via WebSocket /ws/build/{sid} or SSE /api/sessions/{sid}/logs (polling with 0.3s sleep). 5. OBSERVABILITY: Every phase completion, evaluator score, and terminal status writes a fire-and-forget row to Supabase via supabase_log.py. 6. PI-SEO LOOP: Scanner clones portfolio repos → produces JSON findings in .harness/scan-results/ → Monitor Agent reads findings, computes deltas, saves .harness/monitor-digests/ → Triage Engine creates Linear tickets for critical/high findings → Auto-PR Engine opens GitHub PRs for auto-fixable items. 7. MCP PATH: Claude Desktop calls pi-ceo-server.js tools via stdio → tools read .harness/ files or call Linear GraphQL API → results returned to Claude Desktop context. 8. HARNESS PERSISTENCE: All session state, lessons, scan results, board minutes, and cron trigger last_fired_at timestamps persist to the .harness/ filesystem directory, which survives server restarts but NOT Railway container redeployments (ephemeral disk).",
